        "title": "Records of Headquarters U.S. Air Force (Air Staff)",
        "naId": 653
      }
    ],
    "scopeAndContentNote": "This series consists of moving picture films and video recordings of high altitude balloon tests and flights (including those made with anthropomorphic dummies and by U.S. Air Force personnel); footage of various high-altitude projects such as Project Mogul, Excelsior III, Manhigh, and Stargazer; and interviews with alleged witnesses to the Unidentified Flying Object (UFO) crash site at Roswell, New Mexico. Included also, is the final edited version of the U.S. Air Force video report that was compiled to accompany \"The Roswell Report\" publication issued in 1997.",
    "naId": 566658,
    "functionAndUse": "These records were created or acquired in the process of investigating and gathering research materials to prepare the U.S. Air Force official publications \"The Roswell Reports\" in 1994 and 1997. The reports examined alleged incidents of an Unidentified Flying Object (UFO) crash at Roswell, New Mexico in July 1947.",
    "numberingNote": "Items are numbered from 1 to 44."
